        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "Logic (from the Ancient Greek: λογική, logikḗ), originally meaning \"the word\" or \"what is spoken\" (but coming to mean \"thought\" or \"reason\"), is generally held to consist of the systematic study of the form of inference and arguments. A valid argument is one where there is a specific relation of logical support between the assumptions of the argument and its conclusion. (In ordinary discourse, the conclusion of such an argument may be signified by words like therefore, hence, ergo and so on.) - [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Logic wikipedia]"
